In general, the problem of finding a specific submatrix in a larger matrix is of importance in several computer science disciplines. For example Boolean matrices, and their associated submatrices of 1’s, play a central role in data mining problems such as frequent itemset mining [13]. Moreover, finding a submatrix of 1’s in the adjacency matrix of a graph G corresponds to finding a biclique of G [13]. As the maximum edge biclique problem is NP-complete [10], the complexity of searching for a \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
